{% from "components/section-intro.njk" import sectionIntro %}
{% from "components/section-title.njk" import sectionTitle %}

{{ sectionIntro(name='how-much', backgroundColor='gray-legacy-700', textColor='blue', lineColor='gray-legacy-400') }}

<div class="pb-24 bg-white">
	<div class="container flex flex-col items-center" x-data x-init="(function () { {{ sectionHowMuchTranslation() }} })()">

		{{ sectionTitle(section='sectionHowMuch', name='first', icon='bank.svg') }}

		<div class="flex flex-row px-28 mt-48 space-x-28 w-full">
			<div class="flex relative justify-end items-end pt-24 pr-12 pb-8 w-1/2 bg-blue-gray-200 rounded-xl">
				<h3 class="text-3xl text-blue-gray-800 font-dm-mono">Fixed-based</h3>
				<picture>
					<source srcset="./images/pricing/coins.webp" type="image/webp">
					<source srcset="./images/pricing/coins.png" type="image/png">
					<img src="./images/pricing/coins.png" class="hidden absolute top-0 left-0 h-56 transform -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 md:block" media="(min-width: 960px)" loading="lazy">
				</picture>
			</div>
			<div class="flex relative justify-end items-end pt-24 pr-12 pb-8 w-1/2 bg-blue-gray-200 rounded-xl">
				<h3 class="text-3xl text-blue-gray-800 font-dm-mono">Hourly-based</h3>
				<picture>
					<source srcset="./images/pricing/hourglass.webp" type="image/webp">
					<source srcset="./images/pricing/hourglass.png" type="image/png">
					<img src="./images/pricing/hourglass.png" class="hidden absolute top-0 left-0 h-56 transform -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 md:block" media="(min-width: 960px)" loading="lazy">
				</picture>
			</div>
		</div>
		{#<hr class="mt-20 mb-12 h-40 border-t-0 border-l border-cool-gray-400 md:mb-16 md:h-48">#}
		<div class="flex flex-col mt-24 space-y-4 w-full text-left text-white text-cool-gray-800 md:w-1/2">
			<p class="mb-4 text-2xl text-center">
				Our favourite pricing method is using an
				<strong>hourly-based pricing with a minimum and maximum time range</strong> for each milestone.
			</p>

			<ul class="space-y-2 text-lg list-disc text-cool-gray-700">
				<li>It's difficult to know how much time each task will actually take due to unforeseen circumstances or other project nuances
					<ul class="ml-6 list-disc">
						<li>Fixed amount might not accurately represent the value/work/time</li>
						<li>Hourly rate has usually no boundaries, and therefore may go outside client's budget</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
			</ul>

			<ul class="space-y-2 text-lg list-disc text-cool-gray-700">
				<li><strong>Time range caps the maximum so client knows exactly what the highest cost might be</strong>
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>It also gives our team more breathing room if any task takes take longer than anticipated</strong>
				</li>
			</ul>

		</div>
		<hr class="mb-12 mt-8 h-40 border-t-0 border-l border-cool-gray-400 md:mb-16 md:h-48">
		<p class="mb-4 font-medium text-center text-cool-gray-700 sm:font-normal">Our typical proposal look like this...</p>
		<div class="flex justify-center items-center py-16 w-full bg-blue-400 md:w-auto md:px-32 rounded-4xl">
			<a x-bind:href="window.router.getPath('project-proposal')" data-navigo class="flex flex-row items-center py-3 px-5 space-x-1 font-medium bg-yellow-400 rounded-xl ring-offset-2 transition duration-100 ease-linear focus:ring-2 group focus:ring-offset-gray-legacy-800 focus:ring-yellow-200">
				<span class="leading-none whitespace-nowrap text-gray-legacy-800 group-hover:text-gray-legacy-900">Example of a project proposal</span>
				<i class="transition duration-200 ease-out transform gg-chevron-right text-gray-legacy-800 group-hover:text-gray-legacy-900 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 flex-shrink-0"></i>
			</a>
		</div>


	</div>
</div>

